A drawing composes a `Shape`, a `DisplayList`, a `Position`, and a `Style`. It's a complete
 sub-tree of an overall piece of art.

defs.name: Renderer
defs.docs:
A renderer takes a &Canvas and returns a Vec of bytes.
 This allows for drawings to be saved, passed to a conversion method, etc.

defs.name: render
defs.docs: Take a reference to a canvas, return a byte array

defs.name: save
defs.value: fn (canvas: &Canvas, path: &str, renderer: impl Renderer) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs:
Saves a canvas to disk. Note: Will overwrite any existing file at the `path` you provide.
 * `canvas` - Reference to the canvas you want to save
 * `path` - Full or relative path to where you want to save the file
 * `renderer` - An object that implements the `Renderer` trait

defs.docs:
Curve with single control point at `curve`

defs.name: CubicBezierCurve
defs.docs:
Curve with two control points
 `point` - end point of the line segment
 `curve_a` - control point that influences beginning of line
 `curve_a` - control point that influences end of line
